[Multi-morbidity--fate or chance?].

[Article in German]

Atteslander P(1).

Author information:
(1)UniversitÃ¤t Augsburg.

The increase of life expectancy in post-industrial societies also entails an 
increase in multimorbidity. Self-determination of the population and prevention 
through health organisations are imperative. In this connection different health 
concepts are discussed, although in most cases theoretical concepts concerning 
the health and illness behaviour of the population are missing. Present data 
show that the sphere of social epidemiology must be re-orientated. To this end, 
