manner. Many of the present, often activistic health-programmes are ineffective 
with regard to long-term impacts. There is a need to sound a warning in respect 
of an exaggerated economization of the health system: Self-responsibility and 
self-participation of patients alone cannot substantially stop the largely 
self-generating costs, which result from medical-technological progress on the 
one hand and from pretentious demands on the other hand.

